@NODE Introduction "EGS BootLogo .. Introduction"

Introduction
@{FG FILL}************@{FG TEXT}

@{B}EGS BootLogo v2.0@{UB} is a 24-bit boot picture for EGS systems. EGS v6.2
and v7.x can display this image using the screenmode of your choice,
while booting.

The EGS BootLogo image was created using @{B}Montage24!@{UB} and @{B}EGS-ImageFX@{UB}.

Although @{B}CyBERgraphics@{UB} seems to be the buzzword currently,  my A3000
still enjoys the benefits of both systems, and thus I decided to let
others share the fruits of my labours.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "EGS BootLogo .. Requirements"

Requirements
@{FG FILL}************@{FG TEXT}

To use the BootLogo, you must have VIONA Development's EGS RTG System
v6.2 or v7.x installed.   Previous versions of the EGS system are not
able to display this image on startup.

Of course, EGS requires the usual minimum of WB 2.x, hard drive, etc.
I believe EGS works without a graphics card. Why anyone would want to
is beyond me.

EGS can be found on Aminet in gfx/board. The official EGS FTP site is
orion.etsu.edu.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "EGS BootLogo .. Installation"

Installation
@{FG FILL}************@{FG TEXT}

Place the file "bootlogo" in the drawer EGS:Monitors/ and reboot.

Simple, huh?

The image is designed to be displayed on a 736x576 24-bit screen.

You can use the EGS v6.2+ utility @{B}DisplayAdjust@{UB} to set the logo's
screenmode. Simply select the screenmode from the listview gadget
and click the "LogoMode" button below. Save changes and Exit.

DisplayAdjust has been renamed @{B}Tweaker@{UB} under EGS v7.x. Both these
programs should be found in EGS:Prefs/ directory.

@ENDNODE

